## Data Source

Ball-by-ball IPL match data from **[Cricsheet.org](https://cricsheet.org)** — 1243 matches from IPL 2008 to 2026, in JSON format.

---

## Caveats & Honest Limitations

- **Correlation, not causation** — scoring was already trending upward before 2023; the Impact Player rule accelerated an existing trend rather than being the sole cause
- **Model ceiling** — T20 cricket's inherent variance means even the best features can only get pre-match winner prediction to ~50%, and post-powerplay to ~59%. This is not a modeling failure — it reflects the sport's genuine unpredictability
- **No player availability data** — injuries, squad changes, and player form on match day are not in Cricsheet and would likely be the single biggest improvement to the model
- **Small test set** — 286 test matches (2023–2026) is a relatively small evaluation set; results should be interpreted with appropriate uncertainty

---

## Notebooks Guide

| Notebook                    | Input                           | Output                               | Runtime |
| --------------------------- | ------------------------------- | ------------------------------------ | ------- |
| `01_data_extraction`        | `data/ipl_json/*.json`          | `matches.csv`, `deliveries.csv`      | ~30s    |
| `02_feature_engineering`    | `matches.csv`, `deliveries.csv` | enriched `matches.csv`               | ~10s    |
| `03_impact_player_analysis` | `matches.csv`, `deliveries.csv` | `data.json` (website)                | ~5s     |
| `04_additional_analysis`    | `matches.csv`, `deliveries.csv` | enriched `matches.csv`, player CSVs  | ~90s    |
| `05_modeling`               | `matches.csv`                   | `best_models.pkl`, `model_data.json` | ~20s    |

